\title{Projection is a linear operator}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-08}
\taxon{example}
\import{ela}

\p{Let #{V} be a finite-dimensional real vector space. Let #{u\in V} be a nonzero vector #{u\neq\vec{0}}. Then [projection along #{u}](ela-0013) #{\Proj{u}{-}} is a linear operator on #{V}. To see this, we check
##{\Proj{u}{c_{1}v_{1}+c_{2}v_{2}}=c_{1}\Proj{u}{v_{1}}+c_{2}\Proj{u}{v_{2}}}
for any #{v_{1},v_{2}\in V} due to basic properties of the dot product.}